Stop discrimination and start educating people with real facts. Not your hatred. Please and thank you!
Missing nations. Every Desi nation must be equally respected. Please stop discrimination.

Where the term Desi historically descended from, how this term is still in use even when the Indo-aryan languages separated in to different cultural groups when Indo-Aryans went in to different regions and the languages changed depending on the region.
Please use proper facts before posting informations based on your personal emotional opinions.

A certain percentage of Bhutanis and Nepalese close to Desi nations consider them selves "Desi". Unlike Indians, Pakistanis, Sri lankans and the Maldivians. Also Tamils and Bengalis living to the east side do not consider them selves as Desi.
